Spokesman for DPRK Foreign Ministry on Results of DPRK-U.S. Talks 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Foreign Ministry of the DPRK Friday gave the following answer to a question put by KCNA as regards the DPRK-U.S. talks held in Berlin:
 The talks between the DPRK and the U.S. were held in Berlin in accordance with the agreement reached between the two sides. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The talks took place from Jan. 16 to 18 in a positive and sincere atmosphere and a certain agreement was reached there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We paid attention to the direct dialogue held by the DPRK and the U.S. in a bid to settle knotty problems in resolving the nuclear issue.

Joint New Year Editorial of DPRK Studied 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- A seminar on the joint New Year editorial of Rodong Sinmun, Joson Inmingun and Chongnyon Jonwi titled "Usher in a Great Heyday of Songun Korea Full of Confidence in Victory", a briefing on it, a meeting introducing and supporting it and reading sessions were held in the Czech Republic, Peru, Nepal, Tanzania and Indonesia from Jan. 5 to 11.
 Jaroslav Kafka, chairman of the Paektusan Czech-Korean Friendship Association and chairman of the Czech Group for the Study and Materialization of the Juche Idea, said at the seminar that the great successes made by the DPRK in building a great prosperous powerful nation last year are a brilliant fruition of the Songun politics pursued by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The director of an Indonesian company at the briefing noted that the Songun politics is the most just one conducive to defending the sovereignty and dignity of the country and the nation and protecting the world peace and security. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ram K. Karmacharya, president of the National Press Club of Nepal, at the meeting for introducing and supporting the joint editorial said the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il, the single-minded unity in the DPRK and its self-reliant defence capability firmly guarantee the victory of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Victor Oliva Miguel, general secretary of the Revolutionary Socialist Party of Peru, and Stepen John Maina, vice-chairman of the Tanzanian National Coordinating Committee of the Juche Idea Study Groups, at the reading sessions noted that the brilliant victory won by the DPRK last year gave hope and confidence to the world progressives, adding that they would as ever fully support the struggle of the Korean people.

Special Issue of Information Bulletin Published in Democratic Congo 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- The Group for the Study of Kim Jong Il Juche Idea of Democratic Congo published a special issue of information bulletin titled "Comrade Kim Jong Il is the veteran and tested statesman, a great master in the art of leadership" on Jan. 12 on the occasion of the February holiday.
 It extended warm congratulations to leader Kim Jong Il on the occasion of his birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Introducing his unique mode of creation, the bulletin noted that Kim Jong Il is a great thinker and theoretician and the great leader of the cause of global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Bright is the prospect of the human cause of independence and the cause of socialism thanks to the leadership of Kim Jong Il, the bulletin said, and called on all its members to deeply study the great Juche idea and fully apply it to reality.

Songun Video Column Opened on Internet Homepage of Study Group in U.S. 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- The U.S. Group for the Study of Songun Politics opened a new "Songun video column" on its Internet homepage "The Red Banner of Songun" on Jan. 5.
 The homepage carries the portraits of the three generals of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing full support for the joint New Year editorial of the newspapers of the Workers' Party of Korea, the Korean People's Army and the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League in the DPRK, an article on the homepage said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. Group for the Study of Songun Politics decided to open a new column on its homepage for the purpose of widely introducing the exploits of President Kim Il Sung, Kim Jong Il and anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk, firmly defending socialism and the cause of reunification of Korea, studying and disseminating the Juche idea and conveying news of the anti-U.S. struggle in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We pay high tribute to the Korean people who have won victory after victory in the stand-off with the U.S., single-mindedly united in the idea of attaching importance to the military affairs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Let's add shine to this year marking the 95th birth anniversary of Kim Il Sung and the 75th founding anniversary of the Korean People's Army and launch a dynamic struggle for independence and unity! &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The homepage carried Korean films " Great Life in 1994," "The Brilliant History of the Great Leadership," "The Great Leader Comrade Kim Jong Il Pays an Official Visit to the Russian Federation," "55th Founding Anniversary of the DPRK" and multimedia.

Stop to S. Korea-U.S. FTA Negotiations Demanded 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- The Headquarters of the All-People Campaign for Checking south Korea-U.S. Free Trade Agreement called a press conference in Seoul on Jan. 15 and demanded a stop to the sixth round of negotiations for the conclusion of the FTA, according to the south Korean CBS.
 The organization noted that the south Korean "government" has got nothing in nearly one year since the FTA negotiations began. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Urging the "government" to promptly call off the ruinous negotiations, the organization declared it would show the people's will through rallies and other forms of struggle against the negotiations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Earlier, nine assemblymen from the Democratic Labour Party of south Korea including Kwon Yong Gil and Sim Sang Jong went on a hunger strike in Seoul in demand of a stop to the negotiations.

Jargon of U.S. Forces Commander in S. Korea Flailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- Civic and public organizations of south Korea including the People for Achieving Peace and Reunification, the Reunification Solidarity and the South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification reportedly called a news conference in front of the U.S. military base in Ryongsan, Seoul, on Jan. 11 to denounce the blast of the commander of the U.S. forces in south Korea.
 Speakers at the news conference recalled that he had unhesitatingly let loose the balderdash on Jan. 9 that should the south Korea-U.S. agreement on the transfer of the military base to Phyongthaek by 2008 be miscarried due to political reasons or budget problem, the U.S. would stand up against it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They declared that they would never tolerate his behavior threatening the people but fight against it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The press release read out at the news conference urged him to apologize to the people for his bellicose and arrogant threat and immediately retract the demand for the burden on south Korea for the transfer of the base. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It warned that the people would no more pardon the U.S., if it tried to force unilateral concession and sufferings upon south Korea again.

Anniversary of June Popular Uprising to Be Marked in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- A ceremony was reportedly held in Seoul on Jan. 14 to declare the start of the campaign to commemorate the 20th anniversary of the June Uprising for democracy.
 At the ceremony the committee for promoting the commemorations of the 20th anniversary of the June uprising for democracy referred to the fact that a seminar was held on Jan. 11 to set June 10 as commemoration day, and stressed the need to inherit the fighting spirit of the uprisers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The committee said that from that day it would conduct the commemorations of the 20th anniversary of the uprising across south Korea and abroad and hold "civilians' festival for democracy" in Seoul and provinces and various events including lecture and symposium on June 10. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A declaration on the commemorations of the 20th anniversary of the uprising was read out at the ceremony.

Joint Statement of Parties, Government and Organizations Supported
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- Pyongyang-based papers today carry commentaries in support of the joint statement issued by the political parties, government and organizations in the DPRK for the purpose of ushering in the heyday of the cause of national reunification this year in conformity with the realistic requirement of the development of national history and the desire of the fellow countrymen.
 The main spirit of the statement is that all the Koreans should effect a great upswing in the cause of national reunification by turning out as one in the fulfillment of the three tasks laid down in the joint New Year editorial: attaching importance to the nation, defending peace and achieving unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the call for making this year "a year of attaching importance to the nation, defending peace and achieving unity" is a very opportune patriotic call for reunification, which represents the realistic requirement of the movement for national reunification, the Rodong Sinmun analyst goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now the Koreans in the north, the south and overseas are heading for reconciliation, unity and reunification hand in hand, guided by the idea of "By our nation itself". The anti-reunification forces within and without, however, are desperately clinging to anti-reunification moves, feeling uneasiness about this. The United States is putting pressure upon the south Korean authorities in an effort to throw a snag on the process of inter-Korean reconciliation while maliciously pursuing a hostile policy towards the DPRK with the sinister intention to block up the progress of the June 15 reunification era. With the south Korean anti-reunification forces following the U.S. in this, the peace of the country is endangered and dark clouds are hanging over the movement of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Koreans should lift high the banner of attaching importance to the nation, defending peace and achieving unity, if they are to open the way of security and prosperity of the nation, repulsing the challenges of the anti-reunification forces at home and abroad. Only when the Koreans keep a tight hold on the above three tasks can they defend and promote the interests of the nation, smashing the outrageous interference and pressure of outside forces and the moves of the anti-reunification forces of south Korea for confrontation and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Minju Joson analyst calls upon all the Koreans to accelerate the reunification movement in response to the patriotic appeal to make this year "a year of attaching importance to the nation, defending peace and achieving unity" and turn out in the endeavors to fulfil these three tasks, full of conviction of victory.

Deserved Punishment upon Provokers
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- Forty years have passed since Escort Ship 56 was sent to the bottom of the sea while perpetrating provocations against the DPRK.
 The U.S. imperialists and the south Korean war-hawks had infiltrated 35 naval vessels of various types into the territorial waters of the DPRK on 28 occasions from December 30, 1966 to January 13, 1967. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On January 19, 1967 they sent Escort Ship 56 to the point of north latitude 38 degrees 40.7 minutes and east longitude 128 degrees 26.3 minutes for the purpose of spying out the coast defence forces of the DPRK, 3.9 miles north of the extension of the military demarcation line on the sea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The warship bombarded scores of rounds of shells on coastal area of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A coast artillery sub-unit of the heroic Korean People's Army took a decisive self-defence measure to open fire on and sink the warship at 14:30. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This was a deserved punishment the KPA inflicted on those who were engaged in reckless provocations in gross violation of the Korean Armistice Agreement, defying the repeated warnings on the part of the DPRK side and the protest by the fair public opinion of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The miserable end of Escort Ship 56 clearly shows that the foolish provocations of the U.S. imperialists and the south Korean war-maniacs are bound to meet fiasco and will be visited only with corpses and death.

Dear Fellow of Life
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- The revolutionary poems and songs are the close fellow of the Korean people in their life and struggle.
 Inspired by the full-length epic "Mt. Paektu", lyric "Korea Is Fighting" and songs "My Song in Trench" and "Song of Postwar Rehabilitation and Construction", the Korean people won a victory in the Fatherland Liberation War and made great successes in the building a new country and a rich and powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Last year such famous works as songs "Dear General, Where Are You" and "For the Motherland" and lyrics "Forgive Me", "My Motherland" and "Mother" were disseminated among the working people, youth and schoolchildren, arousing them to creating a new life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Various gatherings reciting and explaining poems and debates to learn from them are being held at the units of all levels, making the whole country cheerful. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This year has witnessed the creation of many poems and words of songs. Among them are a long poem "Song of Korea", poems "Forward, Everybody on General March!" and "Motherland Calls Us to Action" and words of songs "Forward, People in Cheers of Victory of Songun", "Let Us Sing Great Army-People Unity", "Let Us Become Hero Loved by Motherland" and "Victory Draws Near".

Great Programme for Juche-based Literature
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- Many literary works have been created in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, enriching the treasure-house of Juche literature.
 The famous work of Kim Jong Il "On Juche Literature" (January 20, 1992) is the guideline which has been taken in bringing about a rapid development of the Juche literature. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Incorporated in the work are deep-going theories on the building of the Juche-based literature from the view of the times, literature and art to the issue of the heritage of national literature and art, the issue of tradition of the revolutionary literature and art and the issue of portraying the socio-political organism, the leader in particular, which is an eternal description source of the DPRK literature. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also comprehensively clarifies the issues of applying the seed theory of works, description principles and methods and the genres and forms of literature into creation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The last 15 years are a significant period in which the validity and vitality of Kim Jong Il's idea and theory on the Juche-based literature have been fully proved and many literary and art works to be handed down through the times and history created. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them are full-length novels including the cycles of novels "Immortal History" and "Immortal Guidance," and the epic "Our Eternal Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung" and the song "Leader Is Always With Us." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Illusion, verse and intellectual novels have been created in the field of the novels and sonnets of different genres and poems have been written to develop the Korean literature in diversified way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, the Songun-based revolutionary literature has come into being in the Songun era to back the Songun-based politics of the Workers' Party of Korea ideologically and emotionally, thus boosting the Juche-oriented ethology depicting the revolutionary practice in a realistic and truthful way onto higher phase. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Fully reflecting the spirit of the times are the novels "Arms", "Kanggye Spirit" and "With Arms" which are included in the cycle of novels "Immortal Guidance", the full-length novel "Burning Desire", scenarios "Days of Military Service" and "Notes of a Woman Soldier", an epic "The Arms of Mt. Paektu Will Be Immortal", a selection of poems "Song of the Soldier", words of a song "Ours is Soldier Family", "Those We Call on Ahead of Others" and light comedies "Promise" and "Comrade".

Dangerous U.S.-Japan Military Nexus under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- Armed forces of the United States and Japan are staging frequent military maneuvers jointly or separately, exchanging visits to their respective areas. This indicates that their military integration has reached a grave phase. This is a blatant challenge to the humankind aspiring after peace against war. Rodong Sinmun Friday says this in a signed article. It goes on:
 Shortly ago, a U.S.-Japan joint military exercise took place in the U.S. naval base in Sasebo of Nagasaki in the land of Japs for five days and a ceremony of inaugurating a PAC-3 unit, the first of its kind to be deployed in Japan, was held in the U.S. air force base in Kadena of Okinawa at the end of last year. The Japanese reactionaries test-fired in the U.S. new type land to air interceptor missile "Ts-SAM" manufactured in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. and Japanese reactionaries have systematically supplemented and rounded off their joint military operation plan and order of action since the end of the Cold War. They are now becoming undisguised in their moves to spread their operation theatre worldwide, while tightening their military alliance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The military alliance and cooperation being tightened by the U.S. and Japan with increased zeal are aimed at rounding off the U.S.-Japan offensive system targeted against the whole of Asia including Northeast Asia and igniting a new war of aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What merits a more serious attention is that their reinforced military alliance is not targeted against Northeast Asia only. The "joint strategic goal" set by the U.S. and Japan was a prelude to the emergence of the U.S.-Japan alliance for invading the whole world as it meant their shared strategic goals in the military and security fields to cope with what they called "new threats" in the new century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. and Japan pin particular hope on the collusion and tie-up in the field of missile defense, while reinforcing their military alliance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They agreed to deploy the already improved new type interceptor missiles in a U.S. military base in Okinawa and, accordingly, bring additional U.S. troops to it. They concluded an agreement on the expansion of the ballistic missile defense plan which calls for jointly producing interceptor missiles and requires Japan to offer technology of ballistic missile defense to the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Frequent is the drill for getting ready in advance for using the joint missile defense system in an actual war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What draws a particular attention in the tightened military alliance is that the DPRK is made its primary target. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article calls on the world peace-loving people to heighten vigilance against the evermore undisguised moves of the U.S. and Japan to tighten their military nexus and launch a dynamic joint struggle to frustrate it.

Korea, Egypt Cooperate in Post and Telecommunication
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- A communique on cooperation between the Korea Post and Telecommunication Corporation and the Orascom Telecom Holding of Egypt was made public Friday.
 The communique says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The delegation of the Orascom Telecom Holding of Egypt headed by its vice-chairman visited Pyongyang from January 13 to 19, 2007. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the visit, the Korea Post and Telecommunication Corporation and the Orascom Telecom Holding of Egypt discussed the issues related to cooperation in the sector of telecommunication of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Both sides agreed to realize long-term cooperation in the sector of telecommunication of the DPRK in the spirit of South-South cooperation and the principles of mutual respect and non-interference in internal affairs.

Kim Jong Il Gives Field Guidance to Industrial Establishments in Huichon City
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il gave field guidance to industrial establishments in Huichon City.
 The first leg of his guidance was the Huichon Machine-Tool Factory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went round the room devoted to the history of the factory, guided by senior officials of the factory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went round different production processes to learn in detail about the progress made in the technological updating and modernization of the factory and production there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Watching the automated production processes and newly manufactured modern machine-tools, he expressed great satisfaction over the fact that the factory has improved its technical equipment and mass-produced efficient machine-tools in a brief span of time and ensured a high level of cultured practice in the production at the factory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the spot he met with Merited Designers Yun Yong Sam and Son Kwang Won and praised them for having greatly contributed to the manufacture of precision and high-speed machine-tools by making persevering inquiry and sincere efforts. He also highly praised the feats performed by the technicians who have devoted themselves to the building of the socialist country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said the stirring reality of the factory is a precious fruition of the revolutionary spirit of self-reliance and fortitude and a clear proof of the justice and vitality of the WPK's idea of attaching importance to science. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If one wages a tenacious struggle, paying primary attention to the development of science and technology just as the workers of the Huichon Machine-Tool Factory did, it is possible to put the national economy on a Juche-based, modern and scientific basis, he noted, underscoring the need for all domains and units to thoroughly establish a production system based on a high level of science and technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Huichon Machine-Tool Factory, the mother factory of the nation's machine-building industry, occupies an important place in putting the national economy on a Juche-based, modern and scientific basis, he said, underlining the need for it to manufacture and supply more modern machine-tools to different fields and thus make a positive contribution to reinforcing the material and technical foundation of the independent national economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that it is necessary to make sustained efforts to put the production on a high-speed, precision and scientific basis in order to boost the production of efficient modern machine-tools, he stressed the need to wage a brisk mass technical innovation movement to this end. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said the factory should attain a higher goal of manufacturing ultra-modern machines now that its technological updating and modernization process have been wound up in the main and indicated the orientation and ways to do so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to mass-produce modern machinery as required by the new century it is necessary to intensify the drive for developing the technological updating in depth and, at the same time, applying new advanced technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The second leg of his guidance was the Youth Electrical Complex. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He appreciated the feats performed by the party members and other working people of the complex, expressing great satisfaction over the fact that they are mass-producing quality electrical appliances by successfully pushing forward the technological updating at the complex and have spruced up their work sites in a cultural and sanitary manner. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The last leg of his guidance was the Huichon Ceramic Factory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said it is necessary to give fullest play to the factory's production capacity in order to increase the supply of quality porcelain ware to people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The most important task facing the factory is to decisively improve the quality of products, he said, adding in order to successfully settle this problem it is necessary to steadily elevate the level of technical skill of the workers and technicians and, at the same time, widely apply advanced technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly praised the strong patriotic zeal of the workers in Huichon, noting that they are now dynamically advancing towards the eminence of a great prosperous powerful nation with the same vim and vigor with which they took the lead in the "Arduous March," forced march full of confidence and optimism holding aloft the slogan "Let's always be cheerful although our path is thorny." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Pak To Chun, chief secretary of the Jagang Provincial Committee of the WPK, Pak Nam Gi, department director of the C.C., WPK, and Ri Jae Il, first vice department director of the same.
